For my assignment 2, the travel website ive designed is created for the Andromeda Galaxy. It shows 6 planet vacation spots, accompanied by images on the surface. The Orbital Odyssey lets users know the Lunar Cycle Rate, the rating of the planet, and a planet class, explained in the guide.

\*none of the pictures in the assignment (unless clearly drawn by me) are mine I found them on google.

# Planning:

![][image1]  
First, I started with defining and sizing where all of my elements would sit. My placeholder image, a picture of a puffle from Club Penguin, holds my skeletal website together for now. 

![][image2]  
Next, my images and boxes are filled with the needed content. Colours are changed to fit my theme, and I even got some cool planets down too. This part took so long but once completed, I could easily replicate it (Copy and paste it). Unfortunately the puffles didn't make it.

Finally, I filled out the page further with a little onboarding quiz to see what kind of accommodations our users will need. Beside that's an ad for Dr.Zorps planetary guide, which when clicked on brings you to another site to explain the little colourful balls associated with each planet.

# Challenges I Faced and how im just better then them:

- The grid system is so challenging to learn but once you start to understand it and get some going exactly where it needs to be first try is so awesome  
- Resizing said grid system is even worse in my opinion and im not sure if ill ever quite get the hang of that  
- The image slideshow was so so difficult to implement and learn about it took easily an hour or two, but so worth it  
- I couldn't find enough assets of random space/planet pictures (especially cause I didn't use any AI pics to my knowledge) which is why I made the Dr.Zorp site cause I couldn't find any pics of an alien on a jet ski 

I hope to learn more about weird and more unseen effects and things in html and css, to be able to make more unique and different websites.
